This is a basic FAQ ( Frequently Asked Questions)

1. Use python3 on your system in my case python 3.11.7 was used. You can install it in different ways.
	On Windows for example you could manually install it from python.org or use scoop (a windows installation manager) or with scoop installing anaconda and with anaconda (is a package manager and environment manager) installing your desired python version.
2. Install the needed packages for our FlaskApp in the requirements.txt file.
	"pip3 install -r requirements.txt"
